Splunk Offline Docs
===================

Offline browser for Splunk product documentation mirrored from help.splunk.com.
Designed for air-gapped and restricted-network Splunk Enterprise deployments.

Version: 0.4.6 (build 20260703w)
Author: Joe Hagan (joehaga@cisco.com)

Overview
--------

Splunk Offline Docs packages a local copy of Splunk on-premises documentation so
users can search and browse help without reaching the public internet. The app
provides a help.splunk.com-style navigation shell, version picker, dark mode,
and internal link resolution across the bundled HTML topics.

Products included in the default bundle
---------------------------------------

* Splunk Enterprise (latest 10.x line from help.splunk.com)
* Splunk Enterprise Security 8
* Splunk SOAR (on-premises)
* Splunk IT Service Intelligence (ITSI)

Content is scraped from help.splunk.com during bundle build. Cloud-only product
trees (for example SOAR Cloud) are excluded by configuration.

Navigation
----------

* Splunk Offline Docs — browse documentation (all users with app access)
* About — this guide and bundle information (all users)
* Configuration — scrape metrics, manual update, daily check toggle (admin only)

Requirements
------------

* Splunk Enterprise 9.x or later (tested on 9.3.1)
* Disk space for the documentation bundle (typically 700 MB–1 GB+ depending on products)
* For building or updating content on a connected host: Python 3 with scraper
  dependencies (see scraper/requirements.txt)

Install
-------

1. Extract the app tarball into $SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps/:

     tar -xzf splunk_offline_docs.tgz -C $SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps/

2. Fix ownership:

     chown -R splunk:splunk $SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps/splunk_offline_docs

3. Restart Splunk:

     $SPLUNK_HOME/bin/splunk restart

4. Open Splunk Web → Apps → Splunk Offline Docs, or use the app navigation bar.

The documentation HTML lives under:

  appserver/static/docs/

Updating documentation
----------------------

From Configuration (admin):

* Check now — compare local bundle versions against help.splunk.com (requires
  outbound HTTPS from the Splunk server, or run check on a build host)
* Incremental update — fetch missing topics and repair links
* Full refresh — rebuild navigation and re-sync all configured products

Daily auto-check is OFF by default for air-gapped sites. Enable it in
Configuration only if the Splunk instance can reach help.splunk.com on a
schedule.

Settings are stored in:

  local/settings.json

REST API (admin)
----------------

Endpoint prefix:

  /servicesNS/nobody/splunk_offline_docs/offline_docs/

Actions:

* status — bundle paths, versions, last sync metadata
* check — remote version check
* update — start incremental or full sync (POST, mode=incremental|full)
* settings — read/write daily_check_enabled (GET/POST)

Building a bundle (connected build host)
----------------------------------------

  cd Splunk4Offlinedocs
  bash scripts/build_bundle.sh

Transfer artifact to the target Splunk server and install as above.

